{"author":"Joe Oakhart","author_email":"joeoakhart+bot@navapbc.com","author_id":"594c-9dcf-5ad6-4e6d","data":{"body":"Security finding #5 folded in (change 664 rejected: era check at cert's self-chosen commit = rollback gap). RESOLVED as Option B era-at-storage-anchor: key validity evaluated at the SIGNATURE event's introducing commit S (gate-resolved, fail-closed, append-only tickets branch per ADR 0046 L1); era boundaries become operator-stamped tickets-branch log positions (added_at_log_position/revoked_at_log_position + rebar trusted-env helper); revoke-without-pin = compromise kill-switch, revoke-with-pin = routine rotation preserving history; merged_log_commit demoted to code-state claim only. Option A (era-at-HEAD) rejected: collapses the era model, O(history) re-certification per rotation. Produce side (ee0b) unchanged — client-persisted envelope's log position IS the anchor. 4214 carries the remediation (findings #4+#5 ACs added); deferred residuals unchanged (2422 anti-rollback counter, 4e1d transparency log, 5100 threshold)."},"env_id":"ade0f2ef-51cc-45a2-bb97-c09846cd3df5","event_type":"COMMENT","timestamp":1784001129600440001,"uuid":"34a2d9ec-0bcb-4f27-9173-356c0cb0b7e3"}